summary: SummaryHighlightsClean IngredientsVeganSustainable PackagingGive BackRefillableClarins Total Eye Lift Eye Cream is a naturally powerful eye cream with Harungana, a retinol alternative, that targets wrinkles, dark circles & puffiness for a visible lift in 30 seconds*.
details: DetailsBenefitsRefillableVisibly lifts in 30 seconds*Visibly smoothes and firmsVisibly reduces the appearance of dark circles and puffinessVisibly reduces lines + wrinklesLayers well with makeupKey IngredientsExclusive Organic Harungana* extract, nature's retinol, visibly firms + fights wrinkles and helps to smooth + replenishActivated Red Jania Extract visibly liftsPlant Caffeine visibly reduces under eye puffinessOrganic Horse Chestnut* escin visibly minimizes dark circlesAn anti-aging tetrapeptide visibly firms*Organic ingredients are produced in accordance with European regulation (CE 2018/848).Research ResultsImmediate lift effect +10%*Eye wrinkles reduced -13%**82% saw dark circles minimized***82% saw puffiness reduced***80% saw firmer skin*****Clinical test, 38 women, immediate visible results**Clinical test, 35 women, visible results after 28 days***Consumer test, 111 women, visible reduction of signs of fatigue after 3 weeks****Consumer test, 111 women, visible results after 3 weeksItem 2642301How To UseUse morning and/or evening. reviews.headline: Love the texture!
reviews.comments: I definitely do notice a subtle difference in my under eyes when i apply this!! I love how the texture feel thick and not thin - I don't know for the price if it's that noticeable but I will keep using!

reviews.headline: Total eye lift
reviews.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I've been using Clarins Total Eye Lift for a few weeks now, and I'm really impressed. The texture is lightweight but rich enough to feel nourishing, and it absorbs quickly without leaving any greasy residue. After applying, my under-eye area feels smoother and looks more refreshed, almost like I've had extra sleep.

I've noticed a subtle lift and less puffiness in the mornings, which makes a big difference in how bright my eyes look. Fine lines appear softer too, especially when I use it consistently.

reviews.headline: Just ok
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This was a travel / sample size given to me to try and it was ok nothing super special I feel like it was just like any other eye cream . There is no scent the packaging is easy to use . But for the price I don't feel like it was effective it did hydrate a little .

reviews.headline: Very nice eye cream!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I really enjoy the Clarins Total Eye Lift. It helps my eyes look refreshed. The cream almost feels gel like, and it goes under makeup beautifully. There is no scent which I appreciate. It is definitely pricy but I think it works great. I received this in exchange for an honest review.

reviews.headline: Very light and moisturizing
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This product feels so good. It's smooth to apply and doesn't leave weird residue. Really nice product and very light feeling, yet moisturizing. I would absolutely recommend this product. Try it!

reviews.headline: Just meh
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I wanted to love the Clarins Total Eye Lift, but honestly, I didn't notice much of a difference. The texture feels nice and it absorbs well, but as far as results goâ€”no real changes for me. My under eyes look the same as before, no big lift or smoothing effect. For the price, I expected to see at least a small improvement, but it just didn't deliver. Not terrible, justâ€¦ meh.

reviews.headline: Hydrating
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This eye cream is hydrating. My under eyes were dry and make up would not sit well. After 2 weeks of using this cream my makeup sits way better. It doesn't have a strong scent which is a plus. It's also not a thick cream, it feels really nice under the eyes. The eye lift effect it promises I can't really say. But it's a good eye cream.

reviews.headline: Nice eye lift concentrate
reviews.comments: Nice pleasant smell and works great to make my eye wrinkles less noticeable.

reviews.headline: The Clarins Total Eye Lift has become my nighttime must-have
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I've been using the Clarins Total Eye Lift as part of my nighttime routine, and honestly, I'm obsessed. The red pump packaging looks so chic on my vanity and makes it super easy to get just the right amount (no product wasted ðŸ™Œ). The texture feels silky and light but still really nourishing, and it sinks in right away without that sticky feeling. The scent is soft and botanicalâ€”barely noticeable once applied. After sticking with it, I wake up with smoother, hydrated under-eyes that look way more rested (even on the nights I don't sleep enough ðŸ˜…). It's definitely a splurge, but since you only need a tiny amount and the results show, I'd say it's totally worth it.

reviews.headline: Great!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Love this stuff! It's lightweight and a little bit goes a long way. It absorbs into the skin nicely, and it's gentle for that fragile under eye area. I feel like it has definitely given my under eye area a more youthful look - I love it.

reviews.headline: Fantastic lift!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Great product! With this product, I've had a very noticeable lift! Cute packaging. I would love it if they came out with a roller as well. Creamy texture and not a strong smell.

reviews.headline: Worth the investment
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This eye cream actually gave me visible results in the couple weeks I've been using it. While it's definitely an investment, I would say it's worth it if your under eyes need some love. The cream is unscented - important for delicate undereye skin. It has a creamy texture. It made my under eyes noticeably brighter and even got rid of a really stubborn milia that had been there for a long time. Great product.

reviews.headline: Great stuff!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] The cream is a nice texture, and goes on smoothly, drying completely. The cream is not sticky and has a pleasant smell. The product seemed to soften my mom's crows feet and made them less noticeable! Overall, she was very happy so I am too!!

reviews.headline: Loved it!!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I liked the texture of this product. It wasn't too greasy. There wasn't really a scent to it. It helped with my dark circles & wrinkles. I liked the packaging for it. Is a good value for your money. Would recommend.

reviews.headline: Not impressed
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Scent was nice and it went on smooth however I haven't noticed any difference and it made me break out. Maybe it's just my skin type but it felt thick and heavy when I put it on and should have known it would clog my pores.

reviews.headline: Seems to work!
reviews.comments:
[I received this product in exchange for my honest review] Clarins Total Eye Lift feels like a treat â€” it delivers hydration, helps with puffiness and smoothing, and makes my under-eyes look more awake and "put together." It didn't revolutionize my skincare routine, but it earned a spot in it.

If you're in your 30s or 40s, dealing with mild to moderate puffiness or fine lines, and you enjoy a luxury skincare experience, this might be a great fit. But if you're expecting a full-on eye lift in a bottle? This won't quite get you there.

Would I repurchase? Maybe. Depends on how it stacks up against a few other creams I want to try next.

reviews.headline: A def must have for daily routine!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] This eye lifting cream works great. I feel my eyes are a little firmer than before I started using this product about a month ago. A little does go along way. I wouldn't use more than a drop for the right amount.

reviews.headline: Meh
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I didn't notice a difference while using this product. It said that you would see results after 5 minutes and I did not. I only used it consistently for a couple of weeks. I had to search the internet for directions on how to use it. That was super inconvenient. My makeup did not lay well over the product either.

reviews.headline: Easy on the eye area
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] The red tube signifies a notable Clarins product. I found the product is easy to apply and not harsh to the eye area. It really is scentless, which is important for this sensitive area. I normal tube is expensive, I would expect it to do a better job for the price. I did notice that my dark circles lightened up but I expected better fine line reversal.

reviews.headline: Really works!
reviews.comments: [I received this product in exchange for my honest review] I honestly saw a difference in my eyes with this product! I have some bags under my eyes and the start of crows feet, and when I applied this product before bed, I woke up with way smoother skin around my eyes. Very easy to apply, very moisturizing feeling. Didn't really notice any scent.

faceoff_positive.comments:
I'm not one to fall for hype, but Clarins Total Eye Lift had me doing a double takeâ€”literally. Within 30 seconds of applying it for the first time, I saw a visible lift around my eyes. Not hours, not daysâ€”seconds. My under-eye area looked smoother, firmer, and more awake, like I'd just come back from a spa nap or deleted five years off my face.

The texture is silky and lightweight, absorbing quickly without any greasy residue. It layers beautifully under makeup, but honestly, it gave me such a fresh look I didn't even feel the need to reach for concealer.

If you're chasing that "I slept eight hours and drank all my water" glow, this little bottle delivers. It's become my secret weapon for mornings when my eyes need a pep talk.

Final verdict: Clarins Total Eye Lift isn't just skincareâ€”it's a confidence boost in a pump.
faceoff_positive.headline: 30 Seconds to Wow!

faceoff_negative.comments: I have been using this since early July and unfortunately haven't seen the results I was hoping for. I did not see any improvement on lightening my dark circles or reducing some fine lines.  The cream was lightweight, hydrating, and non-greasy formula.  For the cost, I wouldn't purchase again.  Maybe try other one of their products.
faceoff_negative.headline: Disappointed with same dark circles and fine lines
